<span id="freeTextContainer18231787129141704763">This book was amazing , violent ,passionate ,riveting, breathtaking, , scary, sad, adventurous, interesting, funny and did I mention really really violent? I find it strange that there are almost no fiction books written about the Aztec culture .it&apos;s a fascinating culture. With myths, customs and beliefs that will stun you. A culture that was both barbaric and socially complex at the same time. I can&apos;t say enough about this book or praise it too much ,it&apos;s an incredible read it should be way mor</span>
  <span id="freeText18231787129141704763" style="display:none">This book was amazing , violent ,passionate ,riveting, breathtaking, , scary, sad, adventurous, interesting, funny and did I mention really really violent? I find it strange that there are almost no fiction books written about the Aztec culture .it's a fascinating culture. With myths, customs and beliefs that will stun you. A culture that was both barbaric and socially complex at the same time. I can't say enough about this book or praise it too much ,it's an incredible read it should be way more popular than it is. Fans of Wilbur Smith will especially love this novel. Think of it as a mix of the best parts of Wilbur Smith and James clavell, then you'll have an idea what reading this book is like. Highly recommended!</span>
